From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kanaka Raju Nayana <kanaka.raju.nayana@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 22:11:50 +0530
Subject: xe/gsc: guard iosys_map include for old kernels

Use HAVE_LINUX_IOSYS_MAP_H in xe_gsc_submit.h to include iosys-map.h
when available, and fall back to dma-buf-map.h otherwise. This keeps
iosys_map prototypes consistent across 5.15 kernels.

Signed-off-by: Kanaka Raju Nayana <kanaka.raju.nayana@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gsc_submit.h | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gsc_submit.h b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gsc_submit.h
index 1416b57..0267aaf 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gsc_submit.h
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gsc_submit.h
@@ -8,6 +8,13 @@
 
 #include <linux/types.h>
 
+#ifdef HAVE_LINUX_IOSYS_MAP_H
+#include <linux/iosys-map.h>
+#else
+#include <linux/dma-buf-map.h>
+#define iosys_map dma_buf_map
+#endif
+
 struct iosys_map;
 struct xe_device;
 struct xe_gsc;
-- 
